Osun State Governor, Mr Adegboyega Oyetola on Tuesday has ordered all Political Appointees aspiring to contest the 2023 General Elections to with immediate effect resign their appointment. This was contained in a statement made available to newsmen in Osogbo by the secretary to the state government, Prince Wole Oyebamiji. The statement read: “this is sequel to the Executive Council meeting of Wednesday 13th April 2022 and the combined effect of Sections 84 (12) and 29(1) of the Electoral Acts 2022 as well as the Electoral timetable released by the Independent National Electoral Commission”. “Notice is hereby given to ALL Political Appointees in Osun State to comply with the directive of Mr. Governor and the provision of the Law”, the statement stressed.